    {
      "id": "el_5",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 65,
      "y": 125,
      "width": 320,
      "height": 219,
      "text": "Simple ratio: a : b = a/b\nDuplicate ratio: a² : b²\nSub-duplicate: √a : √b\nTriplicate ratio: a³ : b³\nSub-triplicate: ³√a : ³√b\nCompounded: (a:b)×(c:d) = ac:bd\nInverse ratio: b : a\n\nWHY: Ratios are just fractions. Duplicate\nmeans squaring both terms, sub-duplicate\nmeans square-rooting both terms.\n\nEx: Duplicate of 3:5 = 9:25\n    Inverse of 3:5 = 5:3",
      "fontSize": 13,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 13,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 500,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 5,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f0"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Simple ratio: a : b = a/b\nDuplicate ratio: a² : b²\nSub-duplicate: √a : √b\nTriplicate ratio: a³ : b³\nSub-triplicate: ³√a : ³√b\nCompounded: (a:b)×(c:d) = ac:bd\nInverse ratio: b : a\n\nWHY: Ratios are just fractions. Duplicate\nmeans squaring both terms, sub-duplicate\nmeans square-rooting both terms.\n\nEx: Duplicate of 3:5 = 9:25\n    Inverse of 3:5 = 5:3",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
